709424f-a.title: Manhattan: 6th Avenue - 32nd Street (West)
709424f-a.text:
Sixth Avenue, west side, north from Wast 32nd Spreet. At
this date the old ''El'' line has been demolished though the south-
bound station remains. This is at 33rd Street and provides an
entrance to the two department stores here, Gimbels and Saks,
through an enclosed bridgeway. After the amicable adjustment by
these stores, the Hudson Tube officials, the City and ths ''E1''
line authorities, the etatton will be removed. Beyond same
appears the dominant Hersld Square Building.
View 1: March 29, 1939
View 2: April 5, 1939
P. L. Sperr
NO REPRODCTIO14

709420f-a.title: Manhattan: 6th Avenue - 32nd Street (West)
709420f-a.text:
889 to 885 (old No. 533-529) Sixth Ave., at and adjoining the S.W.
corner of West 32nd Street. The 4-story white building, new No. 885
(old No. 529) is Childs Restaurant. In the foreground, is Broadway.
April 22, 1929.
P. L. Sperr.
NO REPRODUCTIONS.

720144f-b.title: Manhattan: 6th Avenue - 32nd Street (West)
720144f-b.text:
Sixth Avenue, north from W. 32nd Street, showing
Greeley Square; the southerly triangular area formed
by Broadway intersecting 6th Avenue. The ''El'' follows
the latter and the Potel McAloin (right) is on the former.
To the left are Gimbels and Saks Dept. Stores. The first
mentioned does not appear. Above the ''El'' station (de-
molished in 1938-9) towers the Herald Scuare Building.
Broadway is to the left.
View 1: December 24, 1936
View 2: April 22, 1929
View 3: April 15, 1940
P. L. Sperr
NO REPRODITTIONS

709423f-a.text:
Manhattan Theatre, Gane's Moving Picture Bouse; Trainor's Hotel.
View on Sixth Avenue north between 32nd and 33rd Streets. West

Mr Gane in front.
